issue since a `SecretKeyFactory` subclass is being used just to call a protected constructor; it seems like that’s okay since it’s part of the protected API with no reflection involved. I need to make this concise.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Refined the dedicated active-class test again:\n\n- `tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bc-fips/2.1.2/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bc_fips/BaseSecretKeyFactoryTest.java`\n\nChanges made:\n\n- Replaced the custom test `KeySpec` with JDK `X509EncodedKeySpec`.\n- This avoids relying on Native Image reflection metadata for a test-defined nested class.\n- The test still reaches the intended `BaseSecretKeyFactory.genericGetKeySpec(...)` branch because `X509EncodedKeySpec` implements `KeySpec` and has a public single-`byte[]` constructor.\n- Kept the direct `Provider.Service`/SPI path to avoid the unrelated Native Image JCE provider verification error from `SecretKeyFactory.getInstance(...)`.\n\nThe test now drives this path:\n\n```java\nsecretKeyFactory.getKeySpec(secretKey, X509EncodedKeySpec.class)\n```\n\nwhich should exercise:\n\n- `Class#getConstructor(Class[])`\n- `Constructor#newInstance(Object[])`\n\ninside `BaseSecretKeyFactory.genericGetKeySpec(...)`.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_08abf9286dad3a460169f9f873a4d481a2bcffe0ae9726bceb\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 974, "output": 1206, "cacheRead": 36352, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 38532, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1777989728694, "responseId": "resp_08abf9286dad3a460169f9f861856081a2a3d67fc8c90de6eb"}}
